# The First Residents · Part Ⅰ


有时候我想，20年后、50年后，这里是蓬勃的绿洲，还是早已
被遗忘的废墟。有时候我想，当仿生人第一次梦见电子羊的那个
夜晚，城里有没有一个展览，关于新宇宙的拓荒者，关于初民，
关于现在的你和我。

Sometimes I wonder, after 20 or 50 years, will this place become a thriving oasis, or a wasteland that has long been forgotten? 

Sometimes I wonder, on the night when androids first dream of electric sheep, will there be an exhibition in the city about the pioneers of the new universe, about the first residents, about you and me at this moment?

#  The First Residents · Part II


I've seen things you people wouldn't believe. 

Attack ships on fire of the shoulder of Orion. 

I watched C-beams glitter in the dark near the Tannhäuser Gate. 

All those moments will be lost in time, like tears in rain. 

——  Roy Batty
Artist: Li Hua     Curator: Li Hua
